Website Content Package
FRP Installations Inc. / Wall Protection Solutions
Prepared for website development handoff

For use with the new website build, content planning, and brand transition work

What this document is for
This is not a refresh of the old FRP Installations website. It is a positioning brief for a new site that
presents the company as a healthcare and institutional interior protection subcontractor and long-term
Wall Protection Solutions brand.

Updated through this planning thread • March 23, 2026

1. Executive Summary
FRP Installations Inc. has outgrown the way its legacy website positions the company. The new site should
present the business as a specialist subcontractor and construction partner for healthcare and institutional
interior protection systems across British Columbia.
Core positioning shift
Move away from “FRP installer” language. Lead with wall protection, hygienic systems, healthcare
experience, supply-and-install accountability, and construction-partner credibility.

What the new website must communicate
• The company is not labour-only and should not be framed as a simple installer.
• The company supplies and installs complete systems and takes responsibility for quality, coordination,
and warranty alignment.
• The business is healthcare-heavy and has substantial real project experience across BC hospitals and
clinics.
• The company understands pre-construction, specs, submittals, shop drawings, product selection, value
engineering, and adjacent trade integration.
• The company is transitioning over the next 12–18 months from FRP Installations Inc. toward Wall
Protection Solutions Inc.
Primary brand language to use
• Wall Protection Construction Partner
• Healthcare Interior Protection Systems Contractor
• Wall Protection &amp; Hygienic Systems Specialist
• Wall Protection Solutions for healthcare and institutional construction
• Supply and installation of wall protection systems, hygienic cladding, FRP/FRL wall systems, wet wall
systems, and architectural specialties
Primary audiences
• General contractors and estimators
• Project managers and site teams
• Architects, consultants, and specification writers
• Healthcare and institutional clients
• Prospective employees and future leadership hires
• Manufacturer partners

2. Direct Guidance for the Web Partner
Instruction to the web partner
This website is not simply copying or polishing the old FRP site. It is a new positioning platform. The
company must be presented as a specialist healthcare and institutional interior protection subcontractor
— broader than FRP, stronger than a product installer, and credible to larger GC’s and design teams.

The designer / developer should understand
• The company competes in the same general niche as WallPro and Liquid Diamond and needs a level of
polish that belongs in that tier.
• The website should feel clean, modern, light, and architectural — more like a healthcare / architectural
systems company than a generic construction company.
• The visual tone should be organized, calm, and credible, with strong project imagery and restrained
color use.
• The company wants to begin introducing “Wall Protection Solutions” across the site while still retaining
the legal and legacy brand recognition of FRP Installations Inc.
• The site should attract larger healthcare and institutional opportunities, new GC relationships, and better
employees.
Recommended homepage hero direction
• Headline: Wall Protection Construction Partner
• Subhead: Specializing in healthcare and institutional interior protection systems across British Columbia.
• Supporting line: Supply and installation of wall protection systems, hygienic wall cladding, FRP/FRL
panels, wet wall systems, and architectural specialties.
• Proof blocks: 700+ projects completed; 16+ UPCC clinics; 20 years of commercial construction
experience; projects across British Columbia; 75%+ healthcare work.

3. Brand Transition Guidance (12–18 months)
The business wants to gradually transition from FRP Installations Inc. toward Wall Protection Solutions Inc.
without losing existing recognition. The website should start that transition now using paired language.
• FRP Installations Inc. | Wall Protection Solutions
• FRP Installations Inc. – A Wall Protection Solutions Company
• Wall Protection Solutions by FRP Installations Inc.
What not to do
• Do not abruptly hide the FRP Installations name.
• Do not build the entire site around FRP as the identity of the company.
• Do not create confusion about who the company is; the transition should feel intentional and gradual.

