7. Homepage Guidance
Recommended content order
• Hero section with clean healthcare / institutional project imagery
• Core proof blocks (700+ projects, 16+ UPCC clinics, 20 years of commercial construction experience,
province-wide projects, 75%+ healthcare work)
• Core systems tiles
• Featured healthcare project (Lily’s Community Health Centre / DTES, approx. $550K)
• Healthcare specialization section
• Manufacturer systems / partners section
• Pre-construction support section
• Why contractors choose us
• Resources / FAQ / blog preview
• Contact / request a quote
Recommended proof blocks
• 700+ Projects Completed

• 16+ Urgent Primary Care Centres
• 20 Years Commercial Construction Experience
• 75%+ Healthcare Projects
• Projects Across British Columbia
• Largest Healthcare Interior Protection Package ~ $550K
Visual design direction
• Overall feel should be clean, light, airy, and architectural — closer to healthcare and modern interiors
than to a heavy industrial contractor site.
• Primary color direction: navy / deep blue, white, light grey, with soft blue or muted teal accents.
• Orange may be used only very lightly if desired, but the site should not feel like a construction safety /
civil / equipment brand.
• Use large project photography, lots of white space, restrained graphic elements, and strong typography.
• The website should feel more like an architectural systems company or healthcare specialty contractor
than a generic builder.

