9. FAQ Page Strategy
Yes, the site should have an extensive FAQ page. It should function more like a technical reference library
for spec, search, and pre-construction traffic than a homeowner FAQ.
FAQ category Example question themes

General company questions

• Do you supply and install or install only?
• What areas do you serve?
• Do you work in active hospitals?
• Are you Worksafe compliant and VRCA members?
Pre-construction / estimating • Can you help with product selection and budget pricing?
• Can you suggest alternates or value-engineered options?

• How early should a wall protection contractor be involved?
• How do you determine the right system for the application?

Submittals / documentation

• Do you prepare submittals, shop drawings, and sample packages?
• Do you provide closeout and warranty documentation?
• How do you manage long lead materials and procurement?

Healthcare / hygienic
systems

• What is the difference between FRP and welded hygienic wall
systems?
• Where should Altro Whiterock be used?
• When are True North or AM-Clad appropriate?
• What should be used in patient washrooms, procedure rooms, OR-
related areas, and autopsy spaces?

Wall protection systems

• What is the difference between Acrovyn and Inpro?
• When should Ricochet be used?
• When is stainless wall protection more appropriate than plastic
systems?

FRP / FRL / decorative
panels

• What is the difference between FRP and FRL?
• Where should Panolam FRL or Formica HardStop be used?
• When should decorative or graphic wall systems be specified?

PVC liner / wet areas /
Division 10

• What are PVC liner systems and where are they typically used?
• When should Avonite Wet Walls be used?
• What products are suitable for healthcare washrooms and wet rooms?
• When should expansion joints and entrance mat systems be specified
and coordinated?

10. Blog / Resources Strategy
A blog / resources section is recommended, but it should be built as a practical technical library rather than
as a casual blog. The goal is to attract spec/search traffic, reinforce technical authority, and support pre-
construction conversations.
Suggested resource article topics
• FRP vs FRL: when to use each
• Altro Whiterock vs FRP in healthcare environments
• Acrovyn vs Inpro wall protection systems
• When welded hygienic wall systems are worth the cost
• Products best suited for hospital washrooms and showers
• When stainless wall protection is the right choice
• Where PVC liner systems should be used instead of FRP
• How wall protection materials should terminate into adjacent finishes
• What architects should know about value engineering wall protection scopes
• How to choose the right crash rail, corner guard, or corridor protection system
Blog / resources rules
• Write for GC’s, spec writers, architects, project managers, and facilities people — not homeowners.
• Use practical, technical, search-friendly titles.
• Tie articles back to real project environments: hospitals, clinics, washrooms, kitchens, utility areas,
corridors, and wet spaces.

• Do not produce fluff content just to have a blog.

