Recommended ‘Why Contractors Choose Us’ talking points
• Supply-and-install accountability
• Healthcare and institutional specialization
• 20 years of commercial construction experience informing project coordination
• Experience with submittals, shop drawings, samples, closeout packages, and procurement
• Ability to recommend the right product for the environment, specification, and budget
• Strong relationships with leading manufacturers without bias toward one system in every condition

12. Product Selection Philosophy (Important Messaging Theme)
A core differentiator of the company is not simply access to multiple brands, but the judgment to choose the
right system for the application. This philosophy should be visible on the website.
Key message to use on the site
We focus on selecting the right system for the environment rather than promoting a single manufacturer
or product. Different wall protection and hygienic systems perform best in different applications, budgets,
and maintenance conditions.

• Factors the company considers: application suitability, specification alignment, budget constraints,
durability, maintenance, transitions into adjacent materials, and long-term performance.
• This is especially relevant in healthcare, where overspecifying can waste budget and underspecifying
can create performance problems.

13. Careers and Recruitment Content
Because the company wants to attract strong people and grow, the website should include a careers page
that presents the business as a stable, growing specialty contractor with serious healthcare work.
• Mention 700+ projects, 16+ UPCC clinics, major hospital work, and strong long-term opportunity.
• Use practical, hands-on language that appeals to construction professionals, not overly corporate HR
language.

• State that the company is building for the long term and looking for people who want to grow with the
business.

14. Final Notes for Handoff
• The old site should not be used as the content model.
• The new site must make it obvious within seconds that the company is broader than FRP and credible in
healthcare and institutional work.
• The healthcare page is the single most important credibility page on the entire site for larger GC’s.
• C/S, Altro, and Panolam should be visible as key manufacturer relationships, but the company should
still be presented as product-neutral and application-focused.
• The website should begin the brand transition toward Wall Protection Solutions Inc. without losing the
legal / legacy recognition of FRP Installations Inc.
• The FAQ and Resources sections should be treated as strategic business development assets, not filler.

